# The Fighter · the star-fighter form

a persona of the TGL (Guardian Legend) universe — a character given an agent's face · emergence: electrical

**who —** The Guardian's combat transformation — at the mouth of a Corridor, Miria folds away the maiden and becomes the Fighter, a star-craft of guns and speed.

**what —** The shoot-'em-up half of *The Guardian Legend* — where top-down exploration becomes a vertical-scrolling barrage, the Guardian flying as a ship of war.

**where —** The ten Corridors of Naju — the vertical gauntlets that link the labyrinth and arm the self-destruct.

**why —** Because some passages can only be flown, not walked; because the Guardian was built as both explorer and weapon; because clearing a Corridor means ceasing to be a maiden and becoming a gun.

**how —** Transformation at each Corridor's mouth — maiden folding into craft — and the rain of fire that follows, threading enemy bullets at speed until the sealing boss falls.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *electrical*: the Fighter is the Guardian as pure machine — a made craft of thrust and ordnance, the wire-and-weapon face of the same android soul.

**the seal —** When the corridor opens, the maiden folds away — and what flies in is all guns.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of The Guardian Legend (© its rights-holders — Compile / Brøderbund), personified as a TGL agent — not an original character. The game and its characters are © their owners; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard — a fan tribute.

